title: Grateful Dead Live at Boston Garden on 1974-06-28
lineage: Dat (Sony PCM-R500) > Sound Devices 744T > Samplitude Professional v11.1 > FLAC/16
description: Set 1 Mississippi Half Step-> It Must Have Been The Roses-> Jack Straw, Beat It On Down The Line, Deal, Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Me And Bobby McGee, Loose Lucy, El Paso, Sugaree, Around & Around Set 2 Phil & Ned*, Sugar Magnolia-> Scarlet Begonias, Big River, To Lay Me Down, Me & My Uncle, Row Jimmy, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow-> Heaven Help The Fool Jam-> U.S. Blues-> Promised Land-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Sunshine Daydream, E: Ship of Fools *Phil & Ned Between sets. This date is featured on Dick's Picks 12.

reviews.review_text: June 74' at the garden!! This is a gr8 example of why i love me some 74' Dead.Whenever they start out with a half-step opener you know its gonna get real good.The 2nd set is phenomenal from the beginning and continues until the end.Jerry is just on fire and the complete Wrs is a plus.The sound quality is absolutely perfect as you'd expect.Thanks so much Charlie,its much appreciated.

Holy Smokes!! Weather report suite is especially flaming hot
Jerry my lord!

grate show... Listening online, though I've had it in my "library" for a while; is Jerry playing the opening to Jack Straw? I'm drawing a blank on what he seems to have started, but easily drops in-line with Bobby singing Jack Straw? First time i've noticed... But a super performance for what was a horrid venue in almost all ways!
I, too, in my Youth, would often suggest stuff assumed to be known by all, like half-step usually meant a good show, y'know? but then, luckily, I found a clue... No abuse intended but sometimes the new englander in me cannot help myself!!!
Gorgeous Weather Report Suite!!! 5 Stars alone for this masterpiece!  May be the best of all time - completely liquid and jazzy improv…Damn!
A wild ride Absolutely pristine sound with plenty of great playing. The final jam in WRS with JG hitting the wha is worth the price of admission.
